caption.paragraph:
FIGURE 6.
Some details of morphological characters in 

Astragalus durandianus

. 
A–B)
Fruits densely covered by a mixture of black and white hairs (A: 
Hojjat & Zangooie 32262-FUMH
) or wholly by white hairs and on stipe by black hairs (B: 
Ayatollahi & Zangooie 14380-FUMH
); 
C)
Calyx in fruiting stage covered by black hairs (
Rafeie & Zangooei 30651-FUMH
); 
D)
Seed. Scale bars: A–B=5 mm; C=2 mm; D=1 mm.
